

US President George W. Bush arrived here Saturday evening for a three-day visit to China at the invitation of Chinese President Hu Jintao.

Bush's presidential plane Air Force One landed at Beijing's Capital Airport.

This is Bush's third China trip as US president since 2001 and also his first China visit in his second term of office.

Chinese President Hu Jintao and Premier Wen Jiabao are to meet with President Bush, and they will discuss a wide range of issues.

